<HEAD>To Cut the Rigging.</HEAD>
<P>LET A be one Ship, and B the other, and B C the Rigging to be Cut in the Point E.</P>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="proposition">
<HEAD>PROPOSITION I.</HEAD>
<P>The greatest Range of the Piece in the Parabola, the Line of Impulse, the Ascent, or Height of the Rigging to be Cut, and the Angle of Elevation being given. To find the Horizontal Distance, or the Distance from one Ship to the other.</P>
<P><FIGURE>
