<P>Then R:<HI>r</HI> &plus; Z::S:BC, that is rS &plus; Zs / R = BC  in Diag. and Z^2/G = CE in Diag. then Z^2 &plus; PG / G = BC in Diag. that is Z^2 &plus; PG / G = ZS &plus; rS / R that is Z^2R=ZGS &plus; G<HI>r</HI>S &minus; GPR.</P>
